==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Faints
<hw>Faints</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <def>The impure spirit
which comes over first and last in the distillation of whisky; -- the
former being called the <xex>strong faints</xex>, and the latter, which
is much more abundant, the <xex>weak faints</xex>. This crude spirit is
much impregnated with fusel oil.</def> <rj><au>Ure.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fainty</ent>⟦br⟧
